    <div id="dev-intern" class="job">
      <h2>Software Development Intern</h2>

      <p class="meta"><strong>Location:</strong> Salvador/BA - Brazil</p>

      <p class="meta"><strong>Availability:</strong> Immediate</p>

      <p class="meta"><strong>Duration:</strong> 6 months</p>

      <p>Meedan builds digital tools for global journalism and translation. We are a team of designers, technologists and journalists who focus on open source investigation of digital media and crowdsourced translation of social media. With commercial, media and university partners, we support research, curriculum development, and new forms of digital storytelling.</p>
      
      <p>Meedan’s product suite includes Check, which brings newsrooms and citizen journalists together to verify news anywhere in the world; Montage, which focuses on video annotation; Keep, an integrated archiving tool; and Bridge, which enables collaborative teams of translators and cultural experts to translate and contextualize global social media quickly and accurately. Our recent partners have included some of the world’s most innovative digital news initiatives, like AJ+, Animal Politico, ProPublica, First Draft, Bellingcat, Rappler and others. The internship offers an opportunity to build skills and help us enhance the reliability, performance and security of our software, within a small team of competent technologists and designers. Some of the technologies we’re currently using include the following:</p>

      <ul>
        <li>Ruby / Rails, Python to build API services</li>
        <li>PostgresQL and Elasticsearch for data storage</li>
        <li>GraphQL to expose data stores</li>
        <li>React / Redux / Relay to build cross-platform frontends (web, browser extensions, native / hybrid mobile apps, bots)</li>
        <li>Elastic stack and Nagios for log management and application monitoring</li>
        <li>Docker for app deployment</li>
        <li>Jenkins for continuous integration and deployment</li>
      </ul>

      <p>The intern will be assigned relatively independent, discrete projects that they can work on throughout the course of the term, with weekly check-ins with Karim Ratib (CTO). The student should be present at the Meedan office (Rua Marechal Floriano, 28 - Sala 302, Salvador/BA - Brasil). This is a paid internship.</p>

      <h3>Requirements</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Internship candidate must be a university student currently pursuing a bachelor's in engineering, computer science or a related field in their second year or later</li>
        <li>Some experience with Ruby, JavaScript and other mainstream programming platforms</li>
        <li>Professional working proficiency in English</li>
        <li>Experience with Linux</li>
        <li>Ability to quickly learn and use new technologies</li>
        <li>Strong communications and interpersonal skills</li>
        <li>Interested in working in cross-cultural contexts</li>
        <li>Available Monday-Friday for 4-5 hours/daily, 20 hours/week</li>
        <li>The intern should provide their own computer</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Responsibilities</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Apply knowledge gained in computer science courses to real-world challenges</li>
        <li>Participate in fixing bugs and building new versions of our software product</li>
        <li>Implement automated tests with Ruby and/or JS+React</li>
        <li>Execute manual QA testing of the software, developing testing reports and filing tickets</li>
        <li>Support development of test plans and test data for use during testing</li>
        <li>Coordinate group QA testing efforts with the product team as needed</li>
        <li>Join weekly development and product team calls</li>
        <li>Document weekly activities in a report for the development and product teams</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Nice-to-have skills</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Experience with Linux containerization, especially Docker</li>
        <li>Experience with managing and optimizing database technologies, especially PostgreSQL and Elasticsearch</li>
        <li>Experience with open source software development</li>
        <li>Experience with automated testing</li>
        <li>Experience with GraphQL</li>
      </ul>

